{
  "texts": [
    "Step 6: combating low accuracy for less populated labels",
    "Here we attempt to combat the low accuracy for the labels that have a very small sample size.",
    "In these cases, we analyze the co-occurrence of those labels with other labels through an associative rule mining (Apriori) algorithm (Agrawal et al., 1994).",
    "Our idea is to use significant co-occurring labels and artificially predict one label if the other occurs.",
    "For that, we analyze a small human-annotated train dataset (DSD-Clinician-Tweets-Original-Train)."
  ]
}